Class BufferStructure

  • java.lang.Object
    • BufferStructure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BufferStructureInterface
    public class BufferStructure
extends java.lang.Object
implements BufferStructureInterface
    BufferStructure is an object that holds an array of GapBuffer objects. It specifies a cursor_pos in the first dimension so that lines can be accessed and thus individual characters within those lines as we move into the 2nd dimension of the 2-D structure.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Alexander Labell
